### Wrong Deliveries

```
GET  /wrong-deliveries
  No auth. Paginated. ?type=&color=&page=
  Returns unclaimed items only by default
  Response: standard pagination shape with WrongDelivery objects

POST /wrong-deliveries
  JWT required. Multipart form.
  Fields:
    title       → mandatory
    description → mandatory, what the item looks like, where found
    item_type   → mandatory, one of the check values
    color       → optional
    any_marks   → optional, name tags, tears, patterns, anything identifying
    image       → mandatory, jpeg or png, max 5MB
  Side effects:
    compress image → upload to item-images bucket
  Response: { "id": "uuid" }

GET /wrong-deliveries/{id}
  No auth.
  Response: full WrongDelivery object with poster display name

PATCH /wrong-deliveries/{id}/claim
  JWT required. Cannot be the poster.
  Side effects:
    status = claimed
    claimed_by = current user id
  Response: { "message": "Claimed successfully" }
  Errors: FORBIDDEN if poster tries to claim own post
          409 if already claimed

DELETE /wrong-deliveries/{id}
  JWT required. Poster only. Only if status = unclaimed.
  Response: { "message": "Post removed" }
  Errors: FORBIDDEN if not poster
          409 if already claimed — cannot delete

POST /wrong-deliveries/{id}/report
  JWT required.
  Body: { "reason": "string" }
  Uses existing reports table with target_type = "wrong_delivery"
  Response: { "message": "Report submitted" }
```

